headline: Walmart Faces Estée Lauder Lawsuit Testing Marketplace Trust And Controls
summary: Estée Lauder has filed a federal lawsuit against Walmart (NasdaqGS:WMT), claiming counterfeit versions of its branded products were sold on Walmart's online marketplace. The case focuses on third-party sellers and raises questions about Walmart's controls over product authenticity in its e-commerce channel. The dispute arrives as Walmart continues to invest in its digital platform and marketplace model alongside its core brick and mortar operations. For you as an investor, this case relates...
